snippet: Ms. Harris sharply criticized Mr. Biden over his stance on busing and his recent comments on segregationist senators. Here is a transcript of the exchange.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California sharply criticized former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. at the Democratic presidential primary debate on Thursday, talking about her personal history with busing and calling his recent recollections of working with segregationist senators “hurtful.”
abstract: Ms. Harris sharply criticized Mr. Biden over his stance on busing and his recent comments on segregationist senators. Here is a transcript of the exchange.

headline_main: Kamala Harris and Joe Biden Clash on Race and Busing

snippet: Senator Kamala Harris confronted the former vice president in a searing moment over racial equality, and others attacked him on policy and generational divide.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — Joseph R. Biden Jr. repeatedly found himself on the defensive in the Democratic debate on Thursday over his record as well as his personal views, with the most searing moment of the night, and the primary campaign to date, coming when Senator Kamala Harris confronted him over his comments on working with segregationists in the Senate.

snippet: Abortion is one example of a larger problem for Mr. Biden: his inability to escape parts of a nearly 50-year record.
lead_paragraph: For all Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s efforts to focus his campaign on the economy and the middle class, he has been unable to escape his past views on more contentious subjects — particularly abortion, which has become one of the defining issues of the 2020 race.

headline_main: Joe Biden on Abortion and the Hyde Amendment

snippet: During the ’80s and ’90s, Mr. Biden helped shepherd a string of bills that transformed the criminal justice system — and, experts say, hurt America’s black communities.
lead_paragraph: As Joseph R. Biden Jr. makes his third run for the White House, he is being pressed  to answer for his role in legislation that criminal justice experts  say helped lay the groundwork for the mass incarceration that has devastated America’s black communities.
abstract: During the ’80s and ’90s, Mr. Biden helped shepherd a string of bills that transformed the criminal justice system — and, experts say, hurt America’s black communities.

headline_main: Fact-Checking Night 2 of the 2020 Democratic Debates

snippet: Tonight is part two of the first Democratic debate. Join Lisa Lerer and other Times reporters as they chat about what’s happening onstage.
lead_paragraph: Welcome to a special debate night edition of On Politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.

snippet: A big health care experiment for Democrats shows how fiercely doctors and hospitals will fight.
lead_paragraph: For those who dream of universal health care, Washington State looks like a pioneer. As Gov. Jay Inslee pointed out in the first Democratic presidential debate on Wednesday, his state has created the country’s first “public option” — a government-run health plan that would compete with private insurance.
abstract: A big health care experiment for Democrats shows how fiercely doctors and hospitals will fight.
